The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	The Indian Football Association (IFA) Tuesday decided to refer the Snehasish Chakraborty case to the AIFFs Players Status Committee (PSC). The midfielder has alleged that East Bengal forged his signature on the contract to prevent him from playing for Mohun Bagan in the forthcoming season. The Indian Football Association (IFA) is hopeful the matter would be settled before 21 July, the last date for transfers.                 
	 Biswajit Bhattacharya has been retained the Calcutta Port Trust coach for the forthcoming Calcutta Football League.                
